        "subject": "LU-258 Cleanup and reorganize obdfilter-survey",
        "message": "LU-258 Cleanup and reorganize obdfilter-survey\n\nThe goals of this patch:\n\n1) Eliminate repetition.\n\n2) Translate blocks of code to functions for increased readability.\n\n3) Use more descriptive names for functions and variables.\n\n4) Use consistent formatting\n\n5) Update the documentation (README.obdfilter-survey)\n\nThe separate 'libecho' file is deleted because the case-specific code\nis quite small. I don't think having separate scripts for each use-case\nis particularly useful.\n\nThe script should be functionally equivalent to HEAD with two\nexceptions:\n1) For the netdisk case HEAD will create local osc(s) if they do not\nexist already. With the patch netdisk case requires existing local\nosc(s).\n\n2) For case=network use h2$NETTYPE functions to set the oss_nids value.\nIf, for example, we set targets=\"nid00037\" then add_new_uuids will\nfail with something like \"can't parse lustre nid nid00037@gni.\". This\npatch uses the h2$NETTYPE functions from test-framework.sh to set the\noss_nids value. An alternative solution would be to define an OSSNID\nvariable which can be set at the command line or in the script. However,\nI prefer the approach which doesn't require the user to do extra work.\n\nThe XXX: ? style comments are questions I had while doing the cleanup\nand should not be in the final script.\n\nSigned-off-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I274353575666d0f423e52ca343410663d70c07ba\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
